<DOC><DOCNO> AP881212-0289 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-12-12-88 1137EST</FILEID><FIRST>r f BC-ControlData     12-12 0223</FIRST><SECOND>BC-Control Data,0232</SECOND><HEAD>Top Management Changes for Control Data</HEAD><DATELINE>BLOOMINGTON, Minn. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Lawrence Perlman, chief operatingofficer of Control Data Corp.'s Commercial Credit Corp., has beenappointed president and chief operating officer of Control Data, thecomputer company said Monday.   In addition, Thomas C. Roberts, president of Control Data'sSystems and Services Group, will leave the company ``to pursue otherinterests,'' Control Data said. A successor was not immediatelynamed.   Perlman takes over presidential duties from Robert M. Price,chairman and chief executive officer, who has said he wanted to freehimself of responsibility for day-to-day operations and concentrateon long-range strategy, said company spokesman Frank Ryan.   The position of chief operating officer had been vacant, Ryansaid.   In addition, the company also announced that John K. Buckner,executive vice president and chief financial officer, has beenpromoted to vice chairman and retains the title of chief financialofficer.   Control Data provides computer products and services forbusiness, scientific and engineering applications worldwide.   Last month, the company said it may record an earnings loss inthe fourth quarter that ``could nearly equal the profit recordedthrough the first nine months of 1988, which would result inapproximately break-even earnings for the year.''   It attributed the change in earnings' outlook to ``continuedslippages in shipments and acceptances'' in its computer productsdivision.</TEXT></DOC>